.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF56FF961D95FC7298D6FAAF" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF56FF961D95FC729B64FB5B" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961D95FC7299F8FB8E" bold="true" box="[199,462,1014,1040]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Based on the presence of six dorsal striae and a submarginal stria on each elytron, the new species can be classified within 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF56FF961F13FB9F9ACBFBAA" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1899" box="[577,765,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irinus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961F13FB9F9ACBFBAA" box="[577,765,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Copelatus irinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group. Elongate habitus, complete elytral striation and male median lobe without distinct process place 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF56FF961FBBFBBB9BB0FBC6" authority="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek, 2022" authorityName="Jiang &amp; Zhao &amp; Yang &amp; Jia &amp; Hájek" authorityYear="2022" box="[745,902,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miaowangi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961FBBFBBB9BB0FBC6" box="[745,902,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">C. miaowangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="88F27A30BF56FF961EDFFBBB9BD2FBC7" box="[909,996,1087,1113]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF56FF961963FBBB9C89FBC6" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1884" box="[1073,1215,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961963FBBB9C89FBC6" box="[1073,1215,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">C. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex. Based on the shape of male genitalia, the new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="66B560DABF56FF961E18FBE79BE4FBE3" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1899" box="[842,978,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Copelatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961E18FBE79BE4FBE3" box="[842,978,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">C. chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is, however, distinctly bigger than the latter species; and its median lobe has the slender apical part longer (ca. 1/3 of median lobe length), with dorsal side straight and ventral side slightly concave (see 
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF56FF961FCEFB2F9AC6FB5B" box="[668,752,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–38" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1819,1843]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,192,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-23@38.[190,1398,181,1795]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 29–38. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 29, 31, 33, 35, 37. median lobe in lateral view; 30, 32, 34, 36, 38. paramere. 29–30. C. bacchusi (Hainan); 31. C. chinensis (a. Lakeshan, Zhejiang; b. Yanjiajie, Hunan; c. Tainmushan, Zhejiang); 32. C. chinensis (Tianmushan, Zhejiang); 33. C. dentatipenis sp. nov. (a. holotype, Jinggangshan, Jiangxi; b. Guadun, Fujian; c. Mangshan, Hunan); 34. C. dentatipenis sp. nov. (holotype, Jinggangshan, Jiangxi); 35–36. C. felicis sp. nov. (holotype, Baishui, Yunnan); 37. C. diversistriatus sp. nov. (a. holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan; aa. detail of lateral carina with spines; b. Attapeu, Laos; c. NE Mintaingbin Forest Camp, Myanmar); 38. C. diversistriatus sp. nov. (holotype, Pu’er, Yunnan). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411116" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411116/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Figs 31</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="398E07DCBF56FF961E74FB2F9B70FB5B" box="[806,838,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 39–50" captionStartId="39.[151,264,1839,1863]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,207,1804]" captionTargetId="figure-18@39.[192,1395,181,1815]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 39–50. Male genitalia of Copelatus. 39, 41, 43, 45, 47, 49. median lobe in lateral view; 40, 42, 44, 46, 48, 50. paramere. 39–40. C. japonicus (Shanghai); 41. C. malaisei (a. Gaoligongshan, Yunnan; b. Renjiafen, Yunnan); 42. C. malaisei (Renjiafen, Yunnan); 43–44. C. miaowangi sp. nov. (paratype, Liupanshui, Guizhou); 45–46. C. mopanshanensis sp. nov. (holotype, Mopanshan, Yunnan); 47–48. C. nanlingensis sp. nov. (holotype, Dadongshan, Guangdong); 49–50. C. oblitus (Macao). Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412781" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412781/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">43</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF56FF961D95FB4A98D6FAAF" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961D95FB4A99ABFB76" bold="true" box="[199,413,1230,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Collection details.</emphasis>
The specimens of the 
<typeStatus id="7E0EA5FBBF56FF961FCCFB4B9AF8FB77" box="[670,718,1231,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">type</typeStatus>
series were collected at the Yao Shang Reservoir; the bank had mud and sand bottom, with aquatic vegetation; it was slightly polluted, surrounded by agricultural fields (
<bibRefCitation id="C52466A8BF56FF961861FB7798E5FAAF" author="Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L." pageId="11" pageNumber="262" pagination="1 - 23" refId="ref32617" refString="Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (1998) China water beetle survey (1995 - 1998), pp. 1 - 23. In: Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (Eds.) Water beetles of China. Vol. II. Zoologisch-Botanische Gesellschaft in Osterreich and Wiener Coleopterologenverein, Wien, 371 pp." type="book chapter" year="1998">Jäch &amp; Ji 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9AF48D2BF56FF961D95FABF9A3DFAE7" pageId="11" pageNumber="262" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A10A1B59BF56FF961D95FABF9A3DFAE7" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,1437]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis id="93C1C74BBF56FF961D95FABF9978FACB" bold="true" box="[199,334,1339,1365]" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to its collector, Miao Wang (Shenyang, 
<collectingCountry id="D9A25BC9BF56FF961936FABF9C9AFAC8" box="[1124,1196,1339,1366]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="262">China</collectingCountry>
). The specific epithet is a noun in the genitive singular.
